OL,3,CHow could Labour's new workers' rights
OL,4,Clegislation impact you?
OL,6,FBusiness groups argue the Employment
OL,7,FRights Bill could stifle economic
OL,8,Fgrowth, while unions have welcomed a
OL,9,Fnumber of the changes put forward.
OL,11,FDeputy Prime Minister Angela Rayner
OL,12,Finsisted the plans are "good for
OL,13,Fworkers" and "good for businesses".
OL,15,FThe bill will give workers immediate
OL,16,Faccess to sick pay and parental leave,
OL,17,Fas well as bringing in a ban on some
OL,18,Fzero-hour contracts, and most fire and
OL,19,Frehire practices.
