OL,3,CHow could Labour's new workers' rights
OL,4,Clegislation impact you?
OL,6,FThe ban on "exploitative" zero hours
OL,7,Fcontracts will be broadened to apply
OL,8,Fto agency workers, a move welcomed by
OL,9,Funions who had been lobbying for the
OL,10,Fchange.
OL,12,FThe new rules will mean agency workers
OL,13,Fwould have to be offered a contract
OL,14,Fwith a set number of hours a week, and
OL,15,Fthose who choose to be on zero-hours
OL,16,Fcontracts could get compensation if
OL,17,Ftheir shifts are changed last minute.
OL,19,FThe government hasn't laid out what
OL,20,Fkind of time period would be
OL,21,Fconsidered "short notice".
